      "span_text": "Some time ago, LaMuraglia showed that thrombus absorbed more laser light (400 -600 nm) than vessel wall due to the presence of hemoglobin.  Since the energy required to vaporize a clot in air is simple to determine, it seemed that choosing a laser of the appropriate wavelength would be sufficient to safely ablate thrombus."
